   'description': 'Meta is seeking an experienced Executive Administrative Partner to join the administrative team supporting the office of the Chief AI Officer. The person in this role will need to be a problem-solver with extreme attention to detail as well as highly organized given complex needs, heavy volume, and significant projects and tasks across the office. This person will manage a complex calendar alongside project and task-based work. Additionally, the ideal candidate will be support-minded, adaptable, have exceptional communication skills, excel at relationship building and collaboration, and be proactive and resourceful in executing projects and tasks across the team and company. This position is full-time and can be located in NYC or remotely. If remote, the candidate must be willing to work Eastern Standard time.<br/><br/><strong>Responsibilities</strong><br/>Manage complex scheduling and logistics movements<br/>* Manage reactive and proactive scheduling<br/>* Coordinate internal and external meetings<br/>* Prepare expense reports and purchase requisitions<br/>* Travel to support large off-sites as needed<br/>* Support onsite team needs<br/>* Coordinate both domestic and international travel arrangements<br/>* Build cross-functional relationships between departments<br/>* Partner closely with org lead admins<br/>* Communicate key org and company updates to admins and xfn partners<br/><br/><strong>Qualifications</strong><br/>5+ years of relevant experience providing administrative support to 1 or more executives<br/>* 5+ years of relevant experience coordinating travel logistics on behalf of 1 or more executives<br/>* 5+ years of relevant calendar management and expense report management experience for 1 or more executives<br/>* Experience prioritizing multiple projects<br/>* Experience with Microsoft Office and Google Suite Prior or current experience supporting VPs at large scale tech company, particularly in a scaled office<br/>* Consistent track record of ensuring confidentiality and discretion in all partnerships<br/>* Experience driving events and fostering team morale<br/>* Demonstrates attention to detail, responsible, proactive, drives tasks to completion<br/>* Experience independently managing projects, multi-tasking, and changing direction quickly if needed<br/>* Experience building and maintaining trust with leadership and partners<br/>* Experience collaborating and partnering closely with other administrative professionals and key cross functional partners<br/>* Experience in a multi-staff office environment<br/>* Project management experience<br/>* Experience building, managing and influencing cross-functional business stakeholder relationships<br/>* Experience managing logistics across multiple teams<br/>* BA/BS Degree',
