   'description': '<h3>Minimum qualifications:</h3><ul>\n<li>Bachelor\'s degree in a technical field, or equivalent practical experience.</li>\n<li>1 year of experience in program management.</li>\n<li>Experience in data center planning, constraint enforcement, and\nsupply chain management.</li>\n<li>Experience with machine learning infrastructure deployments.</li>\n</ul><br/><h3>Preferred qualifications:</h3><ul>\n<li>Experience with network hardware and data center infrastructure, including liquid cooling and mechanical/electrical supporting systems.</li>\n<li>Experience with physical planning and deployment of machine rack hardware.</li>\n<li>Experience with operations, and mechanical and electrical systems, with a focus on how this supports a supply chain.</li>\n<li>Ability to be an influential member of a highly integrated team composed of both technical and non-technical members.</li>\n</ul><h3>About the job</h3><p>As a Technical Program Manager on the Machine Operations and Deployment Engineering, you will coordinate throughout the capacity planning and server floor deployment domains to ensure feasibility, manage inter-project dependencies, and plan server floor deployments for global Google capacity deployments with a focus on machine learning and AI deployments.</p>The US base salary range for this full-time position is $113,000-$161,000 + bonus + equity + benefits. Our salary ranges are determined by role, level, and location. Within the range, individual pay is determined by work location and additional factors, including job-related skills, experience, and relevant education or training. Your recruiter can share more about the specific salary range for your preferred location during the hiring process.<br/>Please note that the compensation details listed in US role postings reflect the base salary only, and do not include bonus, equity, or benefits. Learn more about <a href="https://careers.google.com/benefits/" target="_blank">benefits at Google</a>.<br/>Please note that the compensation details listed in US role postings reflect the base salary only, and do not include bonus, equity, or benefits. Learn more about <a href="https://careers.google.com/benefits/" target="_blank">benefits at Google</a>.<h3>Responsibilities</h3><ul>\n<li>Assign physical location\'s on the server floor ensuring space/power/cooling/networking constraints are met.</li>\n<li>Manage rack placement deployment feasibility across physical placement, construction, network deployments, and fleet reconfigurations.</li>\n<li>Track and manage dependencies to enable the rack deployment.</li>\n<li>Order, manage and design process and tooling to review for feasibility, infrastructure dependency tracking, and execution.</li>\n</ul>',
